### What was accomplished this cycle

**Targeted literature scan** found 5 new papers directly validating Phase 2 experimental design:

1. **"Knowing Before Saying" (Afzal et al., ACL 2025)** — Probes predict CoT success from hidden states BEFORE any tokens generated (60-76.4% acc). Middle layers most informative. Directly validates Experiment A. Our extension: probing K-cache specifically (not just residual stream) and predicting numeric answer (not binary success).

2. **"Probing for Arithmetic Errors" (EMNLP 2025)** — Correct answers decodable from internal states when text output is wrong. 80-90% error detection. Directly validates Experiment C (WRRA).

3. **"Causality ≠ Decodability" (2025)** — Important methodological caution: decodable ≠ causal. BUT our Phase 1 (causal perturbation) + Phase 2 (decodability probing) combination addresses this concern perfectly. This actually strengthens our argument.

4. **Godey & Artzi (March 2026)** — 95-99% gradient suppression by LM head confirmed. Text is architecturally guaranteed lossy projection.

5. **Barez et al. (Oxford 2025)** — Paraphrased CoT shows NO significant accuracy gap. Warning for Experiment B — may yield null result. Reinforces priority: A > C > B.

